    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes QComics as a QC protocol/workflow for metabolomics data quality assessment, but does not mention parsing Sciex Multiquant TXT export files, file format handling, or automated detection of QCpool sample positions from instrument output. The paper focuses on QC strategy implementation (blank inspection, drift detection, missing value handling, outlier removal, quality markers) rather than software parsing of vendor instrument files.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_analchem_3c03660",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does the QComics package parse Sciex Multiquant TXT export files to identify and locate QCpool samples that were injected at regular intervals across metabolomics or lipidomics sequences?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:52:08.254516+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Sciex Multiquant is not mentioned anywhere in the paper. The paper does not discuss vendor-specific software tools or instrument data export formats.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_analchem_3c03660",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Sciex Multiquant (> v3.0.3)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:52:08.254516+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we have developed QComics, a robust, easily implementable and reportable method for monitoring and controlling data quality",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes QComics as a QC protocol/method, not as a software package with a GitHub repository name 'ricoderks/QComics'. The paper states QComics 'can easily be performed in software that is available to most researchers (e.g., Microsoft Excel and MetaboAnalyst webtool)' \u2014 it is a workflow/protocol, not a named software tool with a specific GitHub identifier. The card conflates the QC protocol with a software implementation.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_analchem_3c03660",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "ricoderks/QComics",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:52:08.254516+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The injection order of samples in the MS system should follow this sequence: (1) Inject five consecutive procedural blank samples... (2) Inject several consecutive QC samples... (3) Analyze real samples in random order and intercalate QCs across the sequence (e.g., one QC after every 10 samples)... (4) Inject five procedural blank samples at the end of the sequence run",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes QC sample injection strategy and monitoring (e.g., time series plots, PCA plots, control charts), but does not describe generation of a 'structured table of QCpool sample positions, injection indices, sequence IDs, and regularity metrics' as a specific output. The paper focuses on visual outputs (plots, figures) and tabulated RSD estimations, not on parsing and tabulating injection sequence metadata.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_analchem_3c03660",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Structured table of QCpool sample positions, injection indices, sequence IDs, and regularity metrics",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:52:08.254516+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate card describes a software tool for parsing vendor instrument files (Sciex Multiquant TXT exports) to extract QCpool injection metadata. The paper describes QComics as a QC protocol/workflow for assessing metabolomics data quality post-acquisition, not as a file parser or sequence metadata extractor.",
        "The card implies QComics is a named software package (with GitHub identifier 'ricoderks/QComics'), but the paper presents QComics as a methodological protocol that can be implemented in generic tools (Excel, MetaboAnalyst) without specialized software.",
        "The card's research question focuses on automated parsing and detection of QCpool positions from instrument output files. The paper's scope is QC assessment of already-acquired metabolomics data (background correction, drift detection, missing value handling, outlier removal, quality marker monitoring)."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:52:08.254516+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "QComics, a robust, easily implementable and reportable method for monitoring and controlling data quality. The protocol operates in various sequential steps aimed to (i) correct for background noise and carryover, (ii) detect signal drifts and \"out-of-control\" observations, (iii) deal with missing data, (iv) remove outliers, (v) monitor quality markers to identify samples affected by improper collection, preprocessing, or storage, and (vi) assess overall data quality in terms of precision and accuracy.",
      "asbval:note": "The research question is semantically aligned with the paper's core purpose. QComics does compute metrics from QC samples (pooled QC samples are the standard approach mentioned) to assess data quality.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_analchem_3c03660",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "What metrics does QComics compute from QCpool injection data to assess metabolomics or lipidomics study quality?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:52:24.744908+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Sciex Multiquant is not mentioned anywhere in the provided passages. The paper states QComics can be implemented in 'software that is available to most researchers (e.g., Microsoft Excel and MetaboAnalyst webtool)' but does not name Sciex Multiquant.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_analchem_3c03660",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
