    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "method precision and accuracy must be estimated by applying the following acceptance criteria to chemical descriptors detected in QC samples: (i) RSD < 30% for peak intensity, (ii) RSD < 2% for RT, (iii) RSD < 15% for peak width, (iv) m/z error <10 ppm... Additionally, time series plots with predefined tolerance windows can be used to visualize the reproducibility and stability of every quality metrics across the experiment (Figure 4B\u2013E), thereby facilitating the identification of abnormal data points for potential exclusion or reanalysis.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper does compute per-compound metrics (RSD/CV for peak intensity, RT, peak width, m/z error) and generates figures/plots showing these metrics across the analytical run. However, the card claims 'CV' (coefficient of variation) while the paper uses 'RSD' (relative standard deviation) \u2014 these are equivalent metrics but the terminology differs. The outputs are described as 'time series plots' and 'tabulated RSD estimations' rather than a single 'quality overview report,' though the functional intent aligns.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_analchem_3c03660",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Quality overview report (table or figure) showing per-compound CV and signal-trend metrics across QCpool injections",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:52:24.744908+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card specifies 'QCpool positional data' which aligns with the paper's use of pooled QC samples analyzed at intermittent points throughout the analytical run.",
        "The card mentions 'metabolomics or lipidomics' but the paper focuses primarily on metabolomics; lipidomics is not explicitly discussed, though the method is stated to be adaptable to other omics data.",
        "The card's expected output describes a single 'quality overview report' but the paper generates multiple outputs: time series plots, PCA plots, tabulated RSD estimations, and control charts \u2014 not a unified report."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
