    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolomics-data-quality-metrics/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we have developed QComics, a robust, easily implementable and reportable method for monitoring and controlling data quality... To simplify its implementation, this QC protocol can easily be performed in software that is available to most researchers (e.g., Microsoft Excel and MetaboAnalyst webtool), without the need of advanced statistical and programming skills.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms QComics exists and computes quality metrics (RSD, signal trends, outlier detection) and generates visualizations. However, paper explicitly states QComics can be implemented in Microsoft Excel and MetaboAnalyst webtool, NOT as a dedicated R/Python package. Paper does not mention Sciex Multiquant integration or txt export ingestion as a specific input format. The tool's core function (quality metrics computation) is supported, but the implementation details (R/Python package, Sciex Multiquant input) are not.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_analchem_3c03660",
