      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "QC samples are analyzed at the beginning of the analytical run to equilibrate the instrument, as well as at intermittent points throughout the experiment to monitor system stability... Analyze real samples in random order and intercalate QCs across the sequence (e.g., one QC after every 10 samples).",
      "asbval:note": "The paper confirms that QC samples are injected at regular intervals (e.g., every 10 samples) and that signal intensities are used for quality assessment. However, the paper does not specify Sciex Multiquant as the source of input data; it describes a generic UHPLC-MS workflow without vendor specification.",
