    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/quality-control-interval-detection/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Inject several consecutive QC samples to condition the system for the study matrix (i.e., stable chromatographic pressure, reproducible RT, peak area, and peak shape for selected metabolites). This conditioning step usually requires at least five QC samples, although this number might be increased (e.g., 10 injections) when studying complex matrices (e.g., tissues) and when applying less robust analytical approaches (e.g., hydrophilic interaction liquid chromatography, HILIC). (3) Analyze real samples in random order and intercalate QCs across the sequence (e.g., one QC after every 10 samples).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes QC sample injection intervals and validation as core QComics functionality, but does NOT specify Sciex Multiquant as the instrument software or TXT export format. The paper's case study used UHPLC-MS with unspecified vendor.",
