    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/quality-overview-visualization/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To assess method reproducibility, most QC approaches solely rely on (i) inspecting the clustering of QCs in principal component analysis (PCA) scores plots and (ii) computing the relative standard deviation (RSD) for metabolites of interest across QC samples.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper computes RSD (relative standard deviation, equivalent to CV) for QC samples and uses visual inspection (PCA plots, time series plots). However, the paper does not specifically mention 'signal-trend metrics' as a distinct computed metric\u2014it uses visual inspection of time series plots and PCA for drift detection, not a quantified trend metric. The card's framing of 'signal-trend metrics' as a computed output is not explicitly supported; the paper uses qualitative visual trend assessment.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_analchem_3c03660",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "quality-overview-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Generate a rapid visual and tabular assessment of metabolomics or lipidomics study quality by computing per-compound coefficient of variation (CV) and signal-trend metrics from QCpool injection sequences.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:58:27.105710+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/quality-overview-visualization/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "the peak intensity of each chemical descriptor should be plotted with respect to their run order to check for time-related trends in the data (Figure 2A,B). Then, the examination of PCA scores plots enables exploring if samples show a continuous drift (Figure 2C) or a homogeneous distribution (Figure 2D) in the PCA space.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes identification of reproducibility and drift via visual and quantitative assessment of QC samples.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_analchem_3c03660",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "quality-overview-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "This skill enables quick identification of compounds and instrumental phases with acceptable versus poor reproducibility and drift characteristics.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:58:27.105710+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/quality-overview-visualization/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "QC samples are analyzed at the beginning of the analytical run to equilibrate the instrument, as well as at intermittent points throughout the experiment to monitor system stability",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes use of pooled QC samples at sequential intervals throughout the run. However, the paper does NOT mention Sciex Multiquant or any specific software for data acquisition/export. The paper states QComics 'can easily be performed in software that is available to most researchers (e.g., Microsoft Excel and MetaboAnalyst webtool)' but does not specify Sciex Multiquant as the input source. The card's requirement for Sciex Multiquant \u2265v3.0.3 txt export is not supported by the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_analchem_3c03660",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "quality-overview-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Apply this skill when you have sequential QCpool (pooled quality control) samples analyzed with Sciex Multiquant (\u2265v3.0.3) and exported to txt format",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:58:27.105710+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/quality-overview-visualization/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Analyze real samples in random order and intercalate QCs across the sequence (e.g., one QC after every 10 samples). If the sample size is small, the frequency of QC injection may be increased to ensure a minimum of 10% QC samples across the analytical run.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes the requirement for regular QCpool injections at intervals throughout the sequence as a core part of the QComics protocol.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_analchem_3c03660",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "quality-overview-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Study design does not include regular QCpool injections at intervals throughout the analytical sequence.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:58:27.105710+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/quality-overview-visualization/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "Sciex Multiquant is not mentioned anywhere in the paper. The paper describes QComics as a protocol that 'can easily be performed in software that is available to most researchers (e.g., Microsoft Excel and MetaboAnalyst webtool)' but does not specify Sciex Multiquant as a required or recommended input tool. The paper does mention 'UHPLC-MS' analysis but does not name the instrument control or data processing software.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_analchem_3c03660",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "quality-overview-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Sciex Multiquant (name: 'Sciex Multiquant', role: 'Data acquisition and export; processes QCpool samples and exports positional data to txt format for downstream quality assessment')",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:58:27.105710+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/quality-overview-visualization/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "we have developed QComics, a robust, easily implementable and reportable method for monitoring and controlling data quality. The protocol operates in various sequential steps aimed to (i) correct for background noise and carryover, (ii) detect signal drifts and 'out-of-control' observations, (iii) deal with missing data, (iv) remove outliers, (v) monitor quality markers to identify samples affected by improper collection, preprocessing, or storage, and (vi) assess overall data quality in terms of precision and accuracy.",
      "asbval:note": "QComics is confirmed as the tool for quality assessment. The paper confirms it computes RSD (equivalent to CV) and produces visualizations and reports. However, the paper does NOT state that QComics 'parses Sciex Multiquant txt exports'\u2014it states the protocol can be performed in Excel or MetaboAnalyst. The GitHub repository URL is not mentioned in the paper and cannot be verified from the passages provided.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_analchem_3c03660",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "quality-overview-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "QComics (name: 'QComics', repo: 'https://github.com/ricoderks/QComics', role: 'Quality overview generation; parses Sciex Multiquant txt exports, computes CV and trend metrics per compound, and produces summary visualizations and reports')",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:58:27.105710+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/quality-overview-visualization/006",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "method precision and accuracy must be estimated by applying the following acceptance criteria to chemical descriptors detected in QC samples: (i) RSD < 30% for peak intensity, (ii) RSD < 2% for RT, (iii) RSD < 15% for peak width, (iv) m/z error <10 ppm",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly defines RSD thresholds for acceptable quality: <30% for peak intensity, <2% for RT, <15% for peak width.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_analchem_3c03660",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "quality-overview-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "parameters (implicit)",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Coefficient of variation (CV) or relative standard deviation (RSD) threshold for acceptable reproducibility",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:58:27.105710+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/quality-overview-visualization/007",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "This tool generates easily interpretable outputs in the form of figures (e.g., Figures 2\u20134) and tables (e.g., tabulated RSD estimations), which could be annexed to scientific publications for consistent reporting of the data quality.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms QComics produces figures and tables including RSD estimations. However, the paper does not explicitly describe 'signal-trend metrics' as a quantified output\u2014it describes visual inspection of time series plots and PCA plots for trend detection, not a computed trend metric.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10_1021_acs_analchem_3c03660",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "quality-overview-visualization",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Summary visualizations and reports of per-compound CV and signal-trend metrics",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T10:58:27.105710+00:00",
